Below is a concise, rephrased English version formatted like an academic program or list of specializations within a Business degree.
Business Major — Common Specializations


Actuarial ScienceApply probability, statistics and finance to assess and manage risk in insurance, pensions and social programs. Learn data analysis, forecasting, risk table construction and computational methods for research and decision-making.


EconomicsStudy the production, distribution and consumption of goods and services and how individuals and institutions allocate scarce resources. Develop skills in economic research, data analysis, trend monitoring and forecasting for issues such as inflation, interest and exchange rates, employment and public policy.


FinanceFocus on the management and allocation of financial resources for individuals, firms and markets. Topics include corporate and investment banking, budgeting and forecasting, asset–liability management, capital markets, stocks and bonds, and financial institutions’ operations.


International BusinessExamine the structures and institutions that shape the global economy. Coursework covers international economics, global finance, cross-border management, trade law, information systems and international marketing.


ManagementLearn principles and practices for planning, organizing, staffing, leading and controlling organizations. Emphasis on systems thinking, organizational behavior, strategic decision-making and effective managerial practices.


MarketingExplore methods to identify and satisfy consumer and business needs for products and services. Study market research, consumer behavior, product development, pricing strategy, promotion and distribution to design and implement competitive marketing programs.


If you want this as part of a syllabus, course catalog entry, or with suggested core courses for each specialization, tell me which format you prefer.' WHERE id = '91344bff-907c-479e-a1d8-ec3c019eb25e';
