UPDATE public.courses SET offer_letter = 'Fees Applies', entry_requirements_text = 'Curriculum
                                    
                                
                            
                            
                                The Doctor of Philosophy (Ph.D.) in Social Science offers valuable opportunities across many sectors. Graduates may find employment in both the public and private sectors and can fill executive roles in organizations focused on global development. Ph.D. holders in Social Science also serve as advisors to a wide range of businesses.
This program aims to prepare candidates who are:

Knowledgeable and skilled in both the theory and practice of social science disciplines, with a strong foundation in research methods.
Competent in technical tasks and interpersonal communication, able to interact effectively in diverse situations and fulfill responsibilities during their research.
Able to work ethically and to apply personal and digital skills that support social science work within their area of specialization.
Confident leaders who demonstrate responsibility and strong quantitative skills relevant to industry and the broader field of social sciences.
Entrepreneurial and capable of applying their expertise across specialties such as Anthropology, Communication Studies, Economics, Education, Geography, History, Law, Linguistics, Political Science, Sociology, Library Science, Environmental Studies, Development Studies, Computational Social Science, Behavioral Sciences, International Relations, Psychology, Public Relations, Social Work, and Public Administration.' WHERE id = '86cbb8a8-7aad-41f9-a1b1-420f8ee9fe86';
